menu "Board Common"

    config BOARD_LANDSCAPE
        bool "Landscape orientation"
        default n
        help
            Rotate the display 90 degrees for landscape orientation.

            When enabled, LVGL sees swapped dimensions (V_RES x H_RES)
            and the board init code applies the appropriate flush callback
            rotation and touch coordinate transforms.

            The convenience macros BOARD_DISP_H_RES / BOARD_DISP_V_RES
            reflect the logical (post-rotation) dimensions.

    config BOARD_CSI_AE_TARGET
        int "CSI camera auto-exposure target (0 = ISP default)"
        default 110
        range 0 235
        help
            Auto-exposure setpoint for the CSI (OV5647) ISP pipeline, 2-235.
            Higher = brighter; 128 = neutral. 0 leaves the ISP/sensor default.

            Decode is a BAND in captured-crop brightness, not a "brighter is
            better" ramp: it wants crop mean ~168-180 and falls off at BOTH
            ends. Too dim and the AEC reaches for analog gain, whose read-noise
            swamps the black/white module separation; too bright and clipped
            highlights eat into that separation from the other side.

            110 lands mid-band on the two panel types that matter most for
            on-screen scanning -- measured decode-rate 1.00 on a mounted 32" VA
            viewed on-axis (crop mean 180), and 1.00 on a MacBook at -3 (crop
            mean 168-177). Prior guidance here suggested ~60-80; sweeps show
            that range yields crop mean ~110-155 and decode-rate 0.00, so do
            not go there.

            NB: the AEC meters the whole frame while the decoder only sees the
            centre crop, so the target needed for a given crop mean shifts with
            how bright the surround is -- re-measure if the framing changes
            substantially. Applied at camera start.

endmenu
